From: Gaggery Tsai <gaggery.tsai@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 9 Apr 2026 21:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] drm/i915/psr: fix Panel Replay cursor lag via psr_pre/psr_post

Panel Replay has no HW auto-tracking for cursor register changes.
Exit Panel Replay BEFORE plane updates (psr_pre) so the display is
live when cursor registers are written, then re-activate AFTER
(psr_post) to restore power savings.

Signed-off-by: Gaggery Tsai <gaggery.tsai@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
@@ -3112,6 +3112,12 @@
 				wm_optimization_wa(intel_dp, new_crtc_state);
 		}
 
+		/* Panel Replay: exit before plane updates so display
+		 * is live when cursor registers are written. PR has
+		 * no HW auto-tracking like PSR2. */
+		if (psr->panel_replay_enabled && psr->enabled)
+			intel_psr_exit(intel_dp);
+
 		mutex_unlock(&psr->lock);
 	}
 }
@@ -3184,6 +3190,12 @@
 		 */
 		intel_dp->psr.busy_frontbuffer_bits = 0;
 
+		/* Panel Replay: re-activate after plane update.
+		 * psr_pre exits PR so cursor is visible during
+		 * register writes. Now re-enter for power savings. */
+		if (psr->panel_replay_enabled && psr->enabled && !psr->active)
+			intel_psr_activate(intel_dp);
+
 		mutex_unlock(&psr->lock);
 	}
 }
